I moved to the area recently and went to try a few things to bring back home. The jerk chicken was pretty good, but the oxtail was insanely good. Even better though was the goat roti which was delicious. The rice and peas were on point, as well as the steamed veggies. Unfortunately they were out of beef patties but that probably means they sell out fast. The only mediocre thing were the fried plantains which felt hard and dry. The price was totally reasonable. Overall, very impressed. I'm going back soon.

I really wish if I could give this restaurant 0 stars. There is a particular young lady who never give me what I pay for. A few occasions I ordered food and didn’t check my food until I reach home only to discover that I didn’t get what I pay for. On one occasion I returned to the restaurant with the food because she didn’t put in all that I ordered in the box. The young lady was very hostile towards me and told me that she did not charge me for the macaroni and cheese. I explain to her that I ordered the mac & cheese but she messed up my order and I left my wallet at home. She was very rude and refused to give me a piece of macaroni and cheese that cost only $3. I asked for the manager and she refused to call him and I asked her what’s her name and she refused to tell me. I called the restaurant late in the evening and got on to the manager and it seems like he has never dealt with her. So, I had stop going there for a very long time and decided to stop by tonight and to my surprise she did the same thing to me except this time she charged me for the mac&cheese but didn’t give it to me. I am beyond upset off right now. I feel like she did that to me on purpose because she obviously remembers my face. I can’t wait for morning to come so that I can report this restaurant to the city.

Ok. So....The veggie roti I got—-I can’t call it a roti. No chana/chickpeas, no CURRY, no potato. Instead, I got cabbage, corn, green peas, string  beans, and carrots wrapped in a roti skin with no type of sauce. If you’ve had ANY roti (veggie or not) the main things inside is CURRY potato and chickpeas at least. I’ve neverrrr had a roti like this lol. The roti skin was nice and fluffy thankfully, but the chef needs to rework the recipe. This is not a traditional roti. Idk what this is.

This was not a veggie roti. There was just the cabbage that comes on the side with your usual meal. There wasn’t any curry in the roti, not even curry potatoes. This was a disgrace to all roti’s everywhere. I’m not sure if they ran out of food, but definitely did not call to say there wasn’t anything to put in the roti.

Chris is the bomb. First off, their jerk chicken is amazing. It comes in a "dinner" (what many restaurants would call a "meal") with rice/beans, cabbage, and some plantains, and at $9.50 a medium is more food than I've ever been able to eat--and a true pleasure. Order it with the oxtail gravy and plenty of jerk sauce, and you can't find many better meals in the neighborhood.  The sides are solid, though the quality seems to vary a bit by what time of day you go. The cornbread has been both amazing and lackluster in the different times I've gone. The mac n cheese is a good choice too.  Also worth mentioning that the beef patties are probably the best I've had in the neighborhood, and at $2 a piece you've got a good snack with one and plenty of food with two. Overall, would recommend Chris to anyone who isn't afraid to get their hands dirty and enjoy some incredible food.
